article_title: Enterprise Man in Critical Condition After Car Accident
article_text:
A 26-year-old Enterprise man is in critical condition after a one-vehicle accident Saturday night.

The Clarke County Sheriff's Department says the wreck happened around midnight on South Street in Enterprise. The vehicle flipped several times and landed in the parking lot of the air vent building. Air Care carried him to University in Jackson. The Sheriff's Department is still investigating what led to this accident.
